# ===================================
# FOUNDLY API ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ===================================
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values
# Never commit .dev.vars to version control

# ===================================
# CLERK AUTHENTICATION
# ===================================
# Get these from your Clerk Dashboard: https://dashboard.clerk.com
CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# ===================================
# SUPABASE DATABASE (Optional)
# ===================================
# Only needed if API directly connects to Supabase
# Get these from your Supabase Dashboard: https://supabase.com/dashboard
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# ===================================
# EMAIL SERVICE (Optional)
# ===================================
# For sending emails via API
RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key_here

# ===================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# ===================================
# 
# 1. FILE NAMING:
#    - For local development: Copy this to .dev.vars
#    - For Cloudflare Workers: Use wrangler secrets for production
#    - Environment variables are bound through wrangler.jsonc
#
# 2. CLOUDFLARE WORKERS SETUP:
#    - Variables are defined in worker-configuration.d.ts
#    - Durable Objects: INSTITUTION_DRAFT, ADMIN_REGISTRY_DO
#    - D1 Database: FOUNDLYDB
#    - KV Namespace: DOMAIN_CACHE
#
# 3. CLERK SETUP:
#    - Create account at https://clerk.com
#    - Create new application
#    - Copy publishable key and secret key from API Keys section
#    - Used for authentication in API endpoints
#
# 4. DEPLOYMENT:
#    - Use `wrangler secret put CLERK_SECRET_KEY` for production
#    - Use `wrangler secret put CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` for production
#    - Other secrets as needed: SUPABASE_URL, RESEND_API_KEY
#
# ===================================
# CLOUDFLARE WORKERS BINDINGS
# ===================================
# These are automatically bound by Cloudflare Workers:
# - FOUNDLYDB (D1 Database)
# - DOMAIN_CACHE (KV Namespace)  
# - INSTITUTION_DRAFT (Durable Object)
# - ADMIN_REGISTRY_DO (Durable Object)
#
# See wrangler.jsonc for binding configuration
#
# ===================================
# SECURITY REMINDERS
# ===================================
# - Never commit actual keys to version control
# - Use different keys for development, staging, and production
# - Use wrangler secrets for production deployments
# - Rotate keys regularly for security
